    <scopecontent>
      <head>Scope and Content</head>
      <p>This collection consists of twelve individual manuscript
         leaves on vellum from the same 
         <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href=""><title xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">Latin Missal</title></bibref>, written in 
         <geogname>Italy</geogname>, in the fifteenth century. The
         writing includes a number of decorative red and blue capitals,
         letters written in red in part of the text, and the use of
         abbreviations.</p>
    </scopecontent>
